ActIndian Act
SubjectSetting apart lands for the use and benefit of Wet'suwet'en First Nation in British Columbia.
PrecisOrder setting apart 38.6 hectares (95.4 acres) of lands for a rural addition to reserve, for the use and benefit of the WET'SUWET'EN FIRST NATION, located in the Regional District of Bulkley Nechako, at approximately 13 kilometres northwest of the City of Burns Lake, British Columbia.
